"title": "8634: amen",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8634",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A Hebrew term expressing the ideas of truth and reliability, often used in prayer and adoration.</p>\n<h2>Amen as an expression of worship</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:36\">1CH 16:36</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:21\">EPH 3:21</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:11-Rev7:12\">REV 7:11–7:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh5:13\">NEH 5:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh8:6\">NEH 8:6</a> <em>The repetition of “Amen” here conveys Ezra's intensity of feeling as he read the Book of the Law. The response of the people represents a solemn, formal acceptance of God's commandments</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps72:19\">PSA 72:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:48\">PSA 106:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:5\">ROM 9:5</a> <em>“Amen” can mean either “Yes indeed, it is so” or “So be it”</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:36\">ROM 11:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:25-Rom16:27\">ROM 16:25–16:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:16\">1CO 14:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:3-Gal1:5\">GAL 1:3–1:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:20\">PHP 4:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:17\">1TI 1:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:15-1Tim6:16\">1TI 6:15–6:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:18\">2TI 4:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:20-Heb13:21\">HEB 13:20–13:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:11\">1PE 4:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:10-1Pet5:11\">1PE 5:10–5:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:17-2Pet3:18\">2PE 3:17–3:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:24-Jude1:25\">JUD 1:24–1:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:4-Rev1:7\">REV 1:4–1:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:4\">REV 19:4</a> <em>the worship of heaven</em></p>\n<h2>Amen confirms a grace or blessing</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:18\">GAL 6:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:33\">ROM 15:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor16:24\">1CO 16:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:23\">PHP 4:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:20-Rev22:21\">REV 22:20–22:21</a></p>\n<h2>Amen confirms a vow or action</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer28:5-Jer28:6\">JER 28:5–28:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num5:20-Num5:22\">NUM 5:20–5:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:15\">DEU 27:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:32-1Kgs1:36\">1KI 1:32–1:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer11:1-Jer11:5\">JER 11:1–11:5</a></p>\n<h2>Amen as a title of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:14\">REV 3:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:18-2Cor1:20\">2CO 1:18–1:20</a> <em>The implication is that all God's promises find their fulfilment in Jesus Christ.</em></p>",
